message_1:
Given the following encrypted message using the Hill cipher:
$$
\begin{pmatrix}
8 & 11\\
3 & 7
\end{pmatrix} 
\begin{pmatrix}
25\\
19
\end{pmatrix}
\equiv 
\begin{pmatrix}
23\\
4
\end{pmatrix} 
\pmod {26}
$$
Find the plaintext message by calculating the inverse of the matrix used to encrypt the message and performing the necessary calculations. Assume that we are working with the English alphabet, so a space is also a character and 'A' is 0, 'B' is 1, and so on.
